1
00:00:01,120 --> 00:00:02,560
Six Minute English.

2
00:00:02,560 --> 00:00:05,779
From bbclearningenglish.com.

3
00:00:07,659 --> 00:00:11,759
Hello, and welcome to Six Minute English from BBC Learning English.

4
00:00:11,759 --> 00:00:12,420
I'm Neil.

5
00:00:12,445 --> 00:00:16,305
And today we're joined by Hannah from the What in the World podcast.

6
00:00:16,305 --> 00:00:17,185
Hey, Neil.

7
00:00:17,185 --> 00:00:18,485
It's great to be back.

8
00:00:18,525 --> 00:00:23,844
So, Neil, do you think you're good at preparing for the future or for unexpected events?

9
00:00:25,900 --> 00:00:28,400
Reasonably good, I suppose.

10
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,820
Depends what kind of event we're talking about.

11
00:00:30,780 --> 00:00:32,400
All kinds of events.

12
00:00:32,400 --> 00:00:38,980
Now, I think I'm pretty organised, but I only have enough food to last me about a week.

13
00:00:39,415 --> 00:00:43,055
And today, we're talking all about preppers.

14
00:00:43,175 --> 00:00:49,855
A prepper is someone who believes that disaster is likely to happen soon, and so they prepare for it.

15
00:00:49,815 --> 00:00:54,495
A prepper might learn survival skills, or they might build a bunker an underground shelter.

16
00:00:54,470 --> 00:00:55,210
Yes.

17
00:00:55,210 --> 00:01:02,030
And recently, many famous billionaires from the tech industry have made the news for building luxury bunkers.

18
00:01:02,150 --> 00:01:06,250
So what these bunkers need to do is to keep you safe from danger.

19
00:01:06,250 --> 00:01:09,290
But they're also like something out of a spy film.

20
00:01:09,290 --> 00:01:10,030
They're huge.

21
00:01:10,225 --> 00:01:14,024
And they've got cool features like gyms or home cinemas.

22
00:01:13,985 --> 00:01:18,245
They allow someone to live a comfortable life while staying safe from danger.

23
00:01:18,245 --> 00:01:20,105
A very comfortable life.

24
00:01:20,225 --> 00:01:26,690
We're going to be talking about these luxury bunkers, the people building them, and what they're so afraid of.

25
00:01:26,650 --> 00:01:29,729
But first, Neil, I've got a question for you.

26
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:37,649
Mark Zuckerberg, the CEO of Meta is building a property in Hawaii,

27
00:01:37,610 --> 00:01:41,914
which is reported to include a huge underground bunker.

28
00:01:41,875 --> 00:01:46,295
So Neil, how much is he reportedly spending on the project?

29
00:01:46,295 --> 00:01:54,850
Is it a) $10,000,000 b) $50,000,000 or c) a $100,000,000?

30
00:01:54,850 --> 00:01:56,930
Well, Hannah, I don't know.

31
00:01:56,930 --> 00:02:01,570
But he's a pretty rich guy, so I think a 100,000,000.

32
00:02:01,570 --> 00:02:05,490
Well, I will reveal the answer at the end of the programme.

33
00:02:05,490 --> 00:02:12,705
Hannah, you've been looking into these luxury bunkers like the one Mark Zuckerberg is reported to be building on What in the World?

34
00:02:12,665 --> 00:02:13,965
What have you discovered?

35
00:02:13,965 --> 00:02:18,864
Well, I was joined by BBC reporter Natalia Jimenez to talk about preppers.

36
00:02:19,120 --> 00:02:25,060
And I started off by asking whether she had ever considered building a bunker and preparing for disaster.

37
00:02:25,060 --> 00:02:29,720
I love this question because I've actually been thinking about it for a while.

38
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:30,340
Fun fact.

39
00:02:30,340 --> 00:02:31,060
That's you.

40
00:02:31,060 --> 00:02:31,780
You're a prepper.

41
00:02:31,780 --> 00:02:32,260
Yes.

42
00:02:32,260 --> 00:02:36,155
When you watch TV in in The US,

43
00:02:36,155 --> 00:02:38,395
when you turn on a kind of US TV channel,

44
00:02:38,395 --> 00:02:41,835
what happens is that there's usually some ads about freeze dried food.

45
00:02:41,835 --> 00:02:42,715
I'm not kidding.

46
00:02:42,715 --> 00:02:48,015
They pop up quite regularly, and it's all about kind of the prepper mentality.

47
00:02:48,190 --> 00:02:50,530
What are you going to do when the apocalypse happens.

48
00:02:50,530 --> 00:02:52,850
Natalia has thought about building a bunker

49
00:02:52,850 --> 00:02:56,610
and getting prepared because she sees adverts for freeze dried food

50
00:02:56,610 --> 00:02:59,750
that would last a long time on TV in The US.

51
00:02:59,950 --> 00:03:04,615
When she talks about the adverts, she says I'm not kidding, which means I'm not joking.

52
00:03:04,615 --> 00:03:09,355
Natalia says that these adverts are part of the prepper mentality.

53
00:03:09,395 --> 00:03:12,715
A mentality is a person's way of thinking about things.

54
00:03:12,755 --> 00:03:17,114
So the prepper mentality would mean thinking about things like a prepper.

55
00:03:17,120 --> 00:03:22,760
Part of the prepper mentality is to question what you would do if the apocalypse happens.

56
00:03:22,880 --> 00:03:27,960
An apocalypse refers to a serious event which causes destruction and change.

57
00:03:28,320 --> 00:03:31,960
So lots of people do think about preparing for bad things.

58
00:03:32,065 --> 00:03:34,025
Natalia's thought about it.

59
00:03:33,985 --> 00:03:40,265
And for tech billionaires like Mark Zuckerberg, they're able to spend a lot of money preparing for disaster.

60
00:03:40,385 --> 00:03:43,605
So do you think they know something we don't?

61
00:03:43,605 --> 00:03:44,825
What are they preparing for?

62
00:03:44,950 --> 00:03:48,490
Let's hear from Natalia again, speaking to me on What in the World.

63
00:03:48,490 --> 00:03:57,470
So the reasons include nuclear tensions, AI risk, climate disaster, essentially any world ending event.

64
00:03:57,510 --> 00:04:02,345
But secondly, it's also a mark of societal status.

65
00:04:02,345 --> 00:04:05,865
So no matter what happens, no matter what comes our way,

66
00:04:05,865 --> 00:04:09,225
if you're a tech billionaire, you're going to be able to live through

67
00:04:09,225 --> 00:04:13,250
that comfortably without compromising your lifestyle,

68
00:04:13,250 --> 00:04:16,209
without compromising the standard that you have.

69
00:04:16,209 --> 00:04:18,529
So because these tech billionaires are

70
00:04:18,529 --> 00:04:21,170
essentially building the future, the fact

71
00:04:21,170 --> 00:04:22,770
that they're so afraid of it,

72
00:04:22,770 --> 00:04:24,950
quote unquote, is telling within itself.

73
00:04:25,145 --> 00:04:29,485
So while tech billionaires are worried about things like climate disaster

74
00:04:29,485 --> 00:04:35,645
or AI, Natalia says that luxury bunkers are also a mark of social status

75
00:04:35,645 --> 00:04:38,225
or status, as we would say in The UK.

76
00:04:38,729 --> 00:04:43,550
Someone's status is the amount of respect or importance given to them by other people.

77
00:04:43,550 --> 00:04:50,190
With their bunkers, tech billionaires would be able to survive without compromising their luxury lifestyle

78
00:04:50,190 --> 00:04:53,010
that means without lowering their standard of living.

79
00:04:53,375 --> 00:04:54,275
Okay.

80
00:04:54,275 --> 00:04:58,035
So now I need to know the answer to that quiz question you gave me, Hannah.

81
00:04:58,035 --> 00:04:58,995
Yes, Neil.

82
00:04:58,995 --> 00:05:01,475
So my question was Mark Zuckerberg,

83
00:05:01,475 --> 00:05:04,915
the CEO of Meta, is building a property in Hawaii

84
00:05:04,915 --> 00:05:08,055
which is said to include a huge underground bunker.

85
00:05:08,229 --> 00:05:10,890
How much is he reported to be spending on the project?

86
00:05:10,890 --> 00:05:15,470
Well, I think I gave option c which was a $100,000,000.

87
00:05:15,510 --> 00:05:16,890
You're right, Neil.

88
00:05:16,890 --> 00:05:20,410
The property is said to include a large underground bunker.

89
00:05:20,410 --> 00:05:23,230
Although Zuckerberg says it's just a little shelter.

90
00:05:23,605 --> 00:05:24,425
Okay.

91
00:05:24,425 --> 00:05:27,785
It's time to recap the language we've learnt during the programme,

92
00:05:27,785 --> 00:05:33,785
starting with prepper someone who thinks disaster is likely to happen soon and so prepares for it.

93
00:05:33,785 --> 00:05:35,385
Kidding means joking.

94
00:05:35,385 --> 00:05:38,205
Your mentality is the way you think about things.

95
00:05:38,529 --> 00:05:43,450
An apocalypse refers to a serious event which causes destruction and change.

96
00:05:43,409 --> 00:05:50,010
Your status or status in society is the amount of respect and importance other people give you.

97
00:05:49,969 --> 00:05:54,705
And if you compromise something, like your lifestyle, you lower the standard of it.

98
00:05:54,705 --> 00:05:57,345
That's it for this episode of six Minute English.

99
00:05:57,345 --> 00:06:00,465
But Hannah, where can people find more What in the World?

100
00:06:00,465 --> 00:06:04,885
Well, you can listen to us wherever you get your BBC podcasts,

101
00:06:05,004 --> 00:06:08,565
or you can watch us on the BBC World Service YouTube channel.

102
00:06:08,820 --> 00:06:11,560
Just search for What in the World in the Studio

103
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,960
or click on the link in the notes for this programme.

104
00:06:13,960 --> 00:06:20,280
And don't forget to test what you've learnt in this programme with the quiz on our website bbclearningenglish.com.

105
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:21,400
Goodbye for now.

106
00:06:21,400 --> 00:06:22,300
Goodbye.

107
00:06:22,340 --> 00:06:24,569
And if you're a prepper, good luck.

108
00:06:25,248 --> 00:06:26,789
Six Minute English.

109
00:06:26,789 --> 00:06:29,589
From b b c learning english dot com.
